{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Glow"], "type": "title", "extent": [59, 68], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [68, 164], "text": ["Simulates a hot glow effect to be used in the Fog context, and\noutputs color and alpha."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [164, 267], "text": ["This operator simulates a hot glow effect to be used in the Fog context,\nand outputs color and alpha."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [267, 410], "text": ["Unlike Halo, which produces a generic, white-light glow, this operator\nis meant for glows around lights, flames, and other hot point sources."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [410, 567], "text": ["The Core parameters control the white hotspot at the very center of the\nglow. For a softer, less hot glow, set the Core Brightness (corebright)\nvalue to 0."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [567, 727], "text": ["The glow color is multiplied by the Opacity (", {"text": ["Of"], "type": "code"}, ") before being mixed with\nthe Surface Color (", {"text": ["Cf"], "type": "code"}, "), so you do not have to take opacity into account\nyourself."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [727, 1067], "text": ["If the Surface Position (", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, "), Position of Eye (", {"text": ["Eye"], "type": "code"}, "), Surface Color (", {"text": ["Cf"], "type": "code"}, ")\nSurface Opacity (", {"text": ["Of"], "type": "code"}, "), and Surface Alpha (", {"text": ["Af"], "type": "code"}, ") inputs are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. If you need\nto access the global variables directly, they are available from the\n", {"text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1067, 1248], "text": ["For a simple glow, connect the color output (", {"text": ["color"], "type": "code"}, ") and the alpha output\n(", {"text": ["alpha"], "type": "code"}, ") to the ", {"text": ["Cf"], "type": "code"}, " and respectively ", {"text": ["Af"], "type": "code"}, " inputs of the ", {"text": ["Output Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/output"}, "\noperator."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1257, 1281], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1281, 1303], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/halo", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/halo"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1303, 1328], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/output"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1248, 1257], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Simulates a hot glow effect to be used in the Fog context, and\noutputs color and alpha."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "glow", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/glow"}, "title": ["Glow"]}